Cholera - Chad, Nigeria, Togo, Zimbabwe 980724220154
Cholera - Africa: WHO guidelines for control 980109220305
Date: Sat, 25 Jul 1998 09:55:54 -0700
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on cholera in Chad, Nigeria, Togo and
Zimbabwe were extracted from the GIDEON software program:
Chad:
The disease is currently or recently reported from Batha, Bet, Biltine,
Chari, Guera, Kanem, Lac, Logone Occidentale, Logone Oriental, Njamena,
Ouaddai and Tandjile
Prefectures.
Nigeria: The disease is currently or recently reported in Abuja, Akwa Ibom,
Anambrea, Bauchi, Bendel, Benue, Borno, Gongola, Imo, Kaduna, Kano,
Katsina, Kwara, Lagos, Niger, Ogun, Ondo, Oyo, Plateau, Rivers and Sokoto
States. Recent activity has also been reported in Kebbi, Taraba and Yobe
States.
Togo: The disease is currently or recently reported from Golfe, Kioto,
Kozah, Lacs, Ogou, Stotuboua, Vo and Yoto districts.

Zimbabwe: 144 cases were reported in 1985. Disease activity was reported
from Manicaland, East and Central Mashonaland, Masvingo and the Midlands
provinces during 1993. There was no activity in these areas during 1994.
Cases (fatal):
Year Chad Nigeria Togo Zimbabwe
1991 13,915 (1,344) 59,748 (7,654)
1992 7,671 (686) 753 (49) 2,039 (105)
1993 225 (0) 19 (2) 5,385 (332)
1994 1,094 (43) 2,859 (313) 47 (5)
1995 1,059 (87) 65 (4)
1996 7,830 (448)* 12,374 (1,193)*** 146 (17)
1997 8,801 (443) 1,322 (134) 42 (7)
1998 824 (49)** 200 (10) 817 (29)
**** *****

* outbreak centered in southern N'Djamena and routes to south
** January to June - with activity in Mayo-Kebbi Prefecture
*** highest number in Kano State
**** Janary to April
***** January to May - activity in Chipinge District (Manicaland Province)
and Chiredzi District (Masvingo Province).
